Class AlertServiceBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.codice.ddf.admin.core.alert.service.internal.AlertServiceBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlertServiceBeanMBean, org.osgi.service.event.EventHandler

    public class AlertServiceBean
extends Object
implements AlertServiceBeanMBean, org.osgi.service.event.EventHandler
    The AlertServiceBean allows Alerts to be retrieved/dismissed by an MBean endpoint and handles Alert Events pushed to the EventAdmin.

      • handleEvent

        public void handleEvent(org.osgi.service.event.Event event)
        Adds an Alert to the collection of current Alerts. The even must have topic Alert.ALERT_EVENT_TOPIC_VALUE and event.getProperty(Alert.ALERT_EVENT_ALERT_PROPERTY) is the Alert to add.

        Already-added Alerts with the same key as the Alert in the event will be overridden. For example, an application may overwrite an existing Alert with the timestamp of when an issue most-recently occurred by specifying the key of the Alert to overwrite.

        Specified by:
        handleEvent in interface org.osgi.service.event.EventHandler

        event -
